cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the preprocessing phase of logic-based reasoning systems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on first-order logic (cs.LO) and its extension with inductive definitions (cs.PL). The use of efficient propositional solvers also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CL). Finally, the implementation and experimental validation aspects of the paper may also relate to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
